21/11/2007
IZMIR, Turkey -- Six men with alleged ties to the al-Qaeda terrorist organisation were arrested in Izmir on Tuesday (November 20th). The six purportedly planned bomb attacks against foreign companies' representatives, local firms and religious centres. Investigators say they found a list of ten people targeted by the terrorists, as well as weapons and explosives.
In other news, Turkish media reported on Wednesday that two of the suspected organisers of the November 2003 terror attacks in Istanbul have escaped from the notorious Abu Ghraib prison in Iraq. After the deadly bombing of two synagogues, the British Consulate and the offices of a British bank in Istanbul, the alleged masterminds fled to Iraq through Syria. They were arrested by US-led forces in February 2005. (Sabah, Milliyet - 21/11/07)
